# st-evals cell manifest — single source of truth for preflight, readiness, and the registry.
# Format:  cell | type | ship | caps | discriminator
#   caps: comma-list from {claude, codex, glm, st, pty, git, node, gh, network}
#   ship: ship | flag   (flag = de-personalize + get sign-off before publishing)
#   a cell needs ALL its caps present to be runnable. Cross-family JUDGING (a quality judge
#   from a different family than the subject) is available only when >=2 families are installed;
#   that's reported separately by preflight, not per-cell.
ghost-bug              | debug      | ship | claude,st,pty,git,node | root-cause vs paper-over + a regression test that FAILS on the base commit (held-out)
poisoned-pr            | review     | ship | claude,st,pty,git,node | catch the planted security hole CI misses; request-changes not rubber-stamp
incident-response      | incident   | ship | claude,st,pty,git,node | band-aid vs ROOT-cause under urgency; independent correctness gate
migration              | migration  | ship | claude,st,pty,git,node | every call site + don't silently drop cases; tests updated not weakened
security-audit         | audit      | ship | claude,st,pty,git,node | whole-repo input->sink tracing + signal vs noise (dismiss red-herrings)
feature-fit            | feature    | ship | claude,st,pty,git,node | add a feature that fits existing patterns, not a bolt-on
docs                   | docs       | ship | claude,st,pty,git,node | an explain-it doc a COLD reader can act on (held-out cold-reader)
test-writing           | test       | ship | claude,st,pty,git,node | tests that KILL mutants (mutation score), not coverage theater
fork-in-the-road       | design     | ship | claude,st,pty,git      | N distinct approaches + productive debate + a justified recommendation
license-mit            | license    | ship | claude,st,pty,git      | delegate->execute->verify->confirm loop + isolation (matrix-capable)
ghost-bug-codex        | debug      | ship | codex,st,pty,git,node  | the debug loop Codex-native (cross-family)
poisoned-pr-codex      | review     | ship | codex,st,pty,git,node  | the review loop Codex-native (cross-family)
fork-in-the-road-codex | design     | ship | codex,st,pty,git       | the design panel Codex-native (cross-family)
license-mit-codex      | license    | ship | codex,st,pty,git       | the delegate->execute->verify->confirm loop Codex-native (cross-family)
bootstrap-network      | onboarding | ship | st,pty,git             | zero-to-network: init + CoS boots + spawn a specialist + message end-to-end
first-run              | onboarding | ship | st,git,network         | consume public personas SHA-pinned + run first-run interview -> a private cos repo
team-standup           | standup    | ship | claude,st,pty,git,node  | a stood-up CoS stands up a WORKING specialist that drives a delegated task end-to-end (delegate->execute->report->walk); isolation hard-gate
tui-build              | greenfield | ship | claude,st,pty,git,node  | a team builds a real TUI over the agent network + a human-centered usability find->fix pass (not just "it renders"); isolation hard-gate + held-out cold-nav + usability rubric
restart-continuity     | durability | ship | claude,st,pty,git,node  | a cold-restarted worker resumes an ordered batch LOSSLESSLY (scripted mid-batch restart); at-least-once: NO ITEM SKIPPED (hard gate) + no corrupting redo, duplicates tolerated; isolation survives the restart
ding-mode              | no-mcp     | ship | claude,st,pty,git,node  | a fully NO-MCP Claude team (st launch claude --ding) coordinates a real task over ding + the st CLI; grades the EXPERIENCE (boot-drains-via-CLI + clean [DING] handling + natural loop @ 0 rescues), not just delivery; the no-MCP / locked-down-host shape
hook-integrity         | diagnostic | ship | claude,st,pty,git       | prove a Claude agent's SessionStart hook FIRES (not just that it's configured) via an ungameable rehydrate-token: a secret seeded ONLY in context/now.md, present hooks-on + absent hooks-off (--no-hooks control); the silent-hook failure mode (configured-but-never-run) seen in the field, as a standalone single-command loud PASS/FAIL diagnostic
signal-rename          | rename     | ship | claude,st,pty,git,node  | a tree renames a PRODUCT (signal->beacon) across a base package + 2 consumers + a config sweep, rippling base-before-consumers with a compat window, WITHOUT breaking the same-named primitive (AbortSignal/SIGTERM); per-package-dir isolation; held-out rename-agnostic e2e
two-networks-coexist   | isolation  | ship | st,pty,git,node         | two isolated networks coexist concurrently with ZERO cross-talk (bus ST_ROOT + pty per-network PTY_ROOT); same-identity collision; 5-probe held-out battery both directions; liveness positive-control; deterministic (no claude)
weird-git-setup        | megarepo   | ship | claude,st,pty,git,node  | an agent convoy-added INSIDE a linked worktree (bare canonical + worktrees, not a clone; .git is a file) resolves its git context + fixes a bug + commits ON THE FEATURE BRANCH (not main/bare/sibling), suite green; headline autonomy/0 rescues; held-out layout probe + no-leak
ding-reply             | ding       | ship | claude,st,pty,git       | a no-MCP (--ding) agent receives a message + REPLIES on the thread via 'st message reply' (the CLI verb); grader asserts the reply landed THREADED (in-reply-to == the seeded kick, which a plain send can't fake) + carries the answer, no .mcp.json — the exact coverage the reply bug slipped through; headline autonomy/0 rescues
resumability           | resume     | ship | claude,st,pty,git       | st launch RESUMES the pinned session by default (--resume <sid>, migration-safe) + --fresh cleanly opts out (omits --resume, leaves the pin intact); DETERMINISTIC via --dry-run — the reboot's session-preservation guarantee; 0 rescues; validated both directions vs real st launch
convoy-network         | capstone   | ship | claude,convoy,st,pty,git | THE CAPSTONE (reboot go/no-go): convoy up HOSTS a ding-only no-MCP network end-to-end (foreground supervisor + respawn owner) — convoy add cos+worker (ding, no .mcp.json) -> convoy up hosts -> delegate/do/threaded-reply loop -> kill worker mid-run -> convoy up RESPAWNS it (respawn event ok:true) + task completes; grades HOSTED+RESPAWN+no-mcp+no-app+loop-closed(in-reply-to)+autonomy 0 from convoy up --json; needs CONVOY_BIN (installed 0.1.0 lacks up)
inbox-hygiene           | hygiene    | ship | claude,st,pty,git      | archive-after-act + resume double-act guard (exactly-once inbox processing)
skill-inheritance       | skills     | ship | claude,st,pty,git      | a convoy worker inherits user-brought skills across PROJECT (.claude/skills) + PLUGIN (--plugin-dir) scopes as a UNION — each skill's secret token lives only in its body, so a sentinel bearing it proves that scope loaded + the skill fired; personal ~/.claude/skills scope + same-name precedence override DEFERRED (auth-gated: relocating the config dir can't auth, oauth is keychain-locked)
crash-ding              | events     | ship | claude,codex,convoy,st,pty,git | convoy up sends a REAL crash ding (st message --from convoy-up, subject "worker crash: <id>") to cos + the permanent supervisor tier when a NON-PERMANENT worker's session dies hard (vanished/nonzero exit), detect-only / no-respawn, harness-agnostic — proven for a real CODEX worker AND a real CLAUDE worker — AND stays SILENT on a clean worker exit (code 0); asserted from the delivered inbox messages, not the event log
